It&#39;s not a bug. You&#39;re just forgetting something very important - with Windows line endings, your lines have a `` before the `
`, so the `
([^
]+
)+` part of your RegEx will also match your blank lines which is why clicking &quot;Find Next&quot; matches everything from the cursor position instead of from the start of the block. 

Go to Edit &gt; EOL Conversion &gt; Unix (LF) and you&#39;ll see that it works now. If you want to support Windows _and_ Unix line endings you&#39;ll have to change every `[^
]` to `[^
]` and every `
` to `?
